<TITLE> DSE posts gains in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com) - Dhaka stocks traded higher in the midday session Monday, spurred by buying pressure on the shares of power companies, banks and pharmaceutical firms. Within one hour of trading, the main share index, DGEN, rallied up to 2036.16 points but a profit-taking move drove the index as low as 2007.05 points before it regained pace in midday trade. Power stock traded upbeat on reports of an increase in the prices of electricity. A 16 percent allocation in the annual development programme for fiscal 2007-08 also buoyed power shares. The DGEN, or general index, climbed 13.47 points or 0.67 percent to 2020.52 at 12.03am. The DSI, or all-share price index, rose 10.48 points or 0.63 percent to 1670.27. Turnover reached Tk 933.03 million by midday. On Sunday, the bourse recorded its highest ever turnover at Tk 2.06 billion. Losers ruled gainers 75 to 60. A total of 18 issues held steady. At 11.51am, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh, leader in turnover at Tk 133.89 million, traded higher at Tk 632 from Sunday's close at Tk 619.25. Prime Bank, BRAC Bank, Square Pharma and Heidelberg Cement followed Power Grid. Only Heidelberg advanced. Prime Bank fell to Tk 762 from Tk 799.25 because of profit-taking. BRAC rose to Tk 751 from Tk 738.75 after a decline the previous day. Square Pharma advanced to Tk 3750 from Tk 3746. Heidelberg grew to Tk 1022.25 from Tk 984.5. The remaining issues in turnoverSoutheast Bank, DESCO, Summit Power, National Bank and Premier Banktraded upbeat. bdnews
